text_retweet: posted @withrepost â€¢ @frizzkidart today's affirmation art: all survivors are brave. all victims are brave. ğŸ’› those who share their stories of surviving sexual violence/intimate partner violence are brave, but those who may not be able to share their stories or don't want to are also brave. no survivor/victim is cowardly and it's their choice what they want to do with their story. you may also wonder why i chose to include the word "victim." not everyone who experiences sexual violence or intimate partner violence feels like a "survivor." if we want to approach this issue in a "survivor-centric" way, then we can't impose the same strong, recovery, survival narrative on every person impacted by sexual violence/ipv. every survivor/victim is different, navigates their trauma differently, and has different perspectives on justice and healing looks like. in looking at the #metoo movement, i've seen a tendency to want to tell all stories the same way, without realizing that all survivors/victims have different intersections in their identity that a) impacts their likelihood to experience violence and b) changes the way experience justice and reconciliation with trauma. every survivor/victim is worthy of love, respect, and support. every survivor/victim is brave no matter how they choose to cope with their trauma. #art #artist #affirmation #illustration #drawing #draw #healing #heal #justice #metoo #feministart #endrapeculture #selflove #brave #torontoartist #feminist

text:
i feel a bit weird writing this because i rarely talk about personal stuff on social media but this is something i want to share this because i will not be the only to feel this way. soon a lot of people will have their reality altered like i did and itâ€™s been fucking rough. i watched one of the first screenings of leaving neverland last saturday. there were only two but itâ€™s going to come out on hbo later this year. 
the simplest way to put it is it fucked me up. like honestly iâ€™ve been physically ill for the past few days just trying to assimilate it. iâ€™m not going to describe the film since everyone will watch it soon but what i will say is i was obsessed with michael jackson in my early teens (anyone who knew me at that age will vouch for the fact that it was ridiculous to the point of insanity), and i always vouched for his innocence, yet after watching this documentary there is now no doubt in my mind that he was a predator. iâ€™m not going to argue with anyone about it right now, because the only thing i can say is â€œwatch the film, then weâ€™ll talkâ€. anyways as i process this i thought it would be a good opportunity to talk about what i think it means for us in the present, because after all heâ€™s dead and weâ€™re the ones left here feeling shitty. i think thereâ€™s many facets to the story, and many questions to ask ourselves and others. the first thing for me as a fan is assimilating that one of the people i admired the most was a very sick person. and then comes the question of how that changes my approach to his art. will i never listen to it because i canâ€™t stop hearing a dark meaning behind every lyric? will i separate the artist and the man, and interpret his art in a way that relates to me?
then i think about the reasons why he did it. was he born sick? did his abusive father make him sick? was he sexually abused as well? was it a combination of being abused as a child, deprived of a childhood because of his stardom and then being given the ability to do it and get away with it through the power we gave him because of his talent? probably. (continued in comment)

text:
here i am, lying awake, not able to stop my racing mind. no matter how long it has been, my heart just can't seem to let go of what i've been through. honestly, i don't believe that my heart will ever truly let go of what happened. 
trauma changes us, it permanently changes us, and for those of us who have lived through it, there really is no such thing as returning to a normal life. once you've been through something truly traumatic, you're forced to live with a new definition of normal. thankfully, this doesn't mean that we can't heal. we can still heal from trauma, not in the sense that all of the pain will be washed away and that we'll be made new, but that we will learn to live again despite all that we've been through. we will learn to live with our scars and do so courageously.

text:
we have heard it a million times. be who you want to be. but the lessons we are often taught when we look to others are more like â€œbe who you want to be as long as it makes me comfortableâ€ â€œbe who you want to be as long as it stays within how you have defined yourself in the pastâ€
â€œbe who you want to be as long as you do not rock the boatâ€
â€œbe who you want to be as long as you are private about itâ€ 
effffffff no. 
who you are itching to embody...do it without shame. without fear. without apology. because you can. and because you are meant to show others the way. 
life is short. live it on your terms, my friend.

michael jacksonâ€™s name is once again being dragged through the mud with claims of child abuse although thereâ€™s fbi files, tapes proving extortion, evidence completely in his favor, multiple witness testimonies, court documents, and a criminal trial with a not guilty verdict except this time heâ€™s not here to defend himself these claims of sexual abuse by two men who came out with their claims after one was denied a job with michaels estate and multiple other deals he filed a 1.3 billion dollar civil suit because of his financial ruin in 2012 the suit was dismissed and michaels estate demands legal fees to be paid. the two men played a part in making a documentary titled â€˜leaving neverlandâ€™ that premiered at sundance this year the documentary used shock factor techniques to persuade the audience into believing mj was some sick creep who preyed on and enjoyed the company of young boys. those who know of these allegations and have looked into the inconsistency of them know that it is far from the truth michael jackson was the complete opposite he was a loving and giving human being. wade robson, the leading man of this documentary and the allegations was the first person called to testify in michaels defense in 2005 wade was an adult at the time swearing michael never harmed him. wade was never contacted to testify in michaels defense he offered to and michael allowed it, so to think michael ever sexually abused him or any child is absurd if michael truly abused him would he had trusted him to be his first witness on the stand that could set the entire tone for his criminal trial? the simple answer to that is no. wade robson is a lying extortionist using michael jacksonâ€™s name to gain fame and money and the media is allowing him to do so this man is making a mockery of the #metoo movement and itâ€™s true victims. itâ€™s time the media tell the truth and expose these men for the liars they are. â€¢

text:
let's get personal for a second..
i have a fair share of people in my life that doubt my dreams. â€¢"it's not going anywhere." â€¢"itâ€™s inconsistent, you can't pay your bills like that." â€¢ "do you really think you'll be on @antmvh1 in front of @tyrabanks ?!â€ what most people aren't aware of is that modeling has absolutely nothing to do with fame and everything to do with self confidence and growth. 
i was first introduced to modeling roughly around the age of 6 by a family friend. or, atleast, what i was told was modeling. 
quickly summarized, i was being used for child pornography. forever scarring me in every way throughout not only childhood, but adulthood as well. i went through life  untrustworthy of men, i flinched when someone unexpectedly bumped into me or went in for a hug. i hated taking pictures or being near a camera. i hated being sexualized in any way. 
at 21, i decided i would no longer let such an evil, sadistic, perverted man determine my self confidence, self love or femininity. so i joined a group online for models and began my search towards liberation. thatâ€™s where i met @sammiechic , an amazing hmua and friend, who has without a doubt held my hand through every detail of every shoot.  donâ€™t get me wrong..a couple years later i still get nervous on set, i still feel a little awkward trying to be sexy, i still flinch when people get too close to me, iâ€™m very selective with who iâ€™ll shoot with, sometimes itâ€™s hard for me to take a genuine compliment and iâ€™m much harder on myself than anyone else has been or ever will be. but the point is, i am healing. 
no, i don't do this to earn fame or money. i do this for myself. making art has aided in my journey towards healing. it's something i never thought i'd be capable of applying myself to, but here i am. because i deserve to feel safe, worthy and beautiful. so do you.

text: if i had to classify my politics i would have to say i identify most with "fourth-wave feminism". fourth-wave feminism began around 2012 and is associated with the belief that all humans areÂ equal. it heavily focuses onÂ intersectionality, pushig for greaterÂ empowermentofÂ traditionally marginalized groupsÂ in society, including women and girls.  fourth-wave feminists advocate for greater representation of these groups in politics and business, and argue that we would have a more equitable society when we incorporate the perspectives of all citizens. whereas earlier feminists fought for and earned women greaterÂ liberation,Â individualism, andÂ social mobility, the new wave furthers the agenda by calling for justice againstÂ assaultÂ andÂ harassment,Â equal pay for equal work, and the freedom to make individual choices over own bodies. Â fourth-wave feminists collaborate and mobilize, often using modern technologies, to publicly speak againstÂ abusers of powerÂ and to provideÂ opportunitiesÂ for girls and women to be properly recognized and compensated for who they are and what they offer. in addition to advocating for women's issues, feminists point out that boys and men should have greater opportunities to be engaged parents to their children, to express their emotions and feelings freely, and to present themselves and their individualities in the ways they wish.

aliza amar was 21-years-old when her life changed forever. she was raped during a job interview. her assailant recorded the assault and distributed the footage as pornography. amar rose from the fog of despair and shame to inspire countless survivors to make their voices heard and address the growing epidemic of rape, sexual assault, and human trafficking. as a leader in the san diego #metoo movement and the founder of breaking the silence together, a san diego-based nonprofit advocating to bring change in the violence against women, she is helping others rise just like she did. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
as a changemaker, aliza works to empower people towards tangible social change. her story is a reminder that we all have the strength within us to become leaders and be the source of change. currently, sheâ€™s working at the las colinas womenâ€™s jail, and a girl rehab facility, inspiring women to turn their life into personal victory. she believes within each woman lies a leader who waits to be born. her biggest aspiration is opening open heart marketplace, a retail store that will be operated by survivors of human sex trafficking and prostitution. it gives survivors the opportunity to support their family by earning their living with power and dignity, and honor. aliza holds a bs in human services and a project management certificate. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €

image description: -
[first slide]
â€œtips for dating someone with anxietyâ€ [second slide]
this is a tumblr post by â€˜mylifelivingwithanxietyâ€™ saying: - reassure them constantly. (this may be annoying but they will be thankful.)
- keep them in the loop of your life. (this means share plans with them. it will keep them at ease.)
- text them when you are on your way, or when you get home. (this may seem obnoxious but their brain will thank you.)
- hugs. (after anxious days something as little as a hug can make things better.)
- triggers. identify them. (this one will be hard. once you figure out what makes them anxious it will help you to make them feel safe.)
- no surprises unless you know it will make them happy. (surprises can be hard to handle for anxious people. it will depend on their anxiety level.)
- change is hard. (try to limit major changes in your relationship if possible. things will change but he ready to help your partner get through it.)
- be there. just be there. (as complex as an anxiety disorder can get, the best thing you can do is to be there and let them know you are.) end image description.

text:
for our fifth issue, overachiever magazine explores the metoo movementâ€™s impact on the asian community. in a traditionally patriarchal, conservative society, a movement that centers around female empowerment, open dialogue about sexual assault, and holding men accountable was sure to make waves. in this issue, our talented contributors share their own metoo stories, show how our culture excuses sexual assault and victim blames, and even show the side we willfully ignore of a prominent historical figure.
i want to thank every woman who shared her story. it takes a lot of courage to give even an opinion on the topic in our community. you are paving the way for a more open, honest discussion and culture.
as always, thank you to the team at overachiever magazine. you are the most brilliant and supportive people.
keep sharing your stories. keep giving your opinions. keep reading, sharing, and supporting asian women.

rehana paul, editor

grandma jean needed a care provider and i knew with every part of my being i was the woman for the job. little did i know she would care for me far more than i would ever care for her.

never did i disclose to her why i moved to her little greek island. yet she clearly knew and became my greatest teacher and closest friend.

she taught me to say, â€œiâ€™ll do whatever i damn well please.â€ with no apologies to follow or the need to explain.

text:
are you a people pleaser? are you tortured by the idea that someone might not like you? i admit, i can struggle with this too. but it's important to recognize that the stress & anxiety that can come from trying to keep up with everyone's opinion of you is not only exhausting, it's unhealthy both emotionally & physically.

for some people, they canâ€™t help to want everyone around them to like them. sometimes, at the sacrifice of their own wants, needs & desires.

people pleasing can look an awful lot like admirably generous or helpful behavior. but thereâ€™s a difference: while true generosity comes from healthy self-regard & a genuine happiness from shared enjoyment, people pleasing comes from a place of lowered self-regard & a need for othersâ€™ approval.

so, decide to block out all the noise, let it go & focus on being a someone that you feel good about. ğŸ’— #loveyourself #selfcare

text:
every thought is a wish and a prayer â€¢
the election of 45 brought on a rage and sadness i didnâ€™t expect. i never thought of myself as an angry person. i got stuck in a cycle of depression. 
in the past two years weâ€™ve seen hate crimes rise, weâ€™ve seen white terrorists plastered all over the media doing their thing, the #metoo campaign and so many other hateful events. itâ€™s triggered so many emotions that i have still not truly dealt with. 
my heart was drowning. 
i just started therapy for the first time and iâ€™m dealing with raw emotions and old wounds reopening. it feels good to release. as i release iâ€™m noticing and learning new things about myself. â€¢
1) being a woman of color in america and really all over the fucking world is scary. i need support.
2) itâ€™s ok to be angry. i need an outlet. 
3) we are affected by not just our immediate environment but also by our society. 
3) ptsd from all this bullshit is real â€¢
in the meantime, iâ€™m focusing on all the good in my life. i have so much to be thankful for. 
self preservation: iâ€™m detoxing from the media. iâ€™m moving my body again. meditation is calming my thoughts. my spiritual practice is softening my edges. 
slowly dropping back into my body. it feels good. i feel more present. â€¢
more thoughts on therapy to come

text:
during meditation i heard spirit speak "you will be given fifth dimensional sight" and i was shown an angelic realm.

the realm i was seeing served humanity with compassion, these angels surrounded our planet and were crying. i was filled with an emotion of deep deep love, it felt like the type of love a mother would feel for her child when her child is suffering, suffering inside themselves from something that is causing great anguish. it was the type of love that resonated as such a strong desire for her child to "know" they are more, to "know" they do not need to suffer, to "know all things are in perfect order" and to trust their inner voice.

when i have these visions (downloads) they are very difficult to describe with words, the emotion attached to the vision is essentially indescribable. the vision (for those who do not or have not opened themselves up to this gift) are very fast and last from our 3 dimensional "time" perspective as a few seconds however, the vision itself is greatly detailed and timeless and the amount of information i'm translating seems impossible to have been received in 1 or 2 seconds. 
the angels are weeping tears of sadness for those who are suffering anguish. they feel each of our individual suffering not because we are "lost" but in the same manor as that of a mother who desires for her child to live a life filled with joy and love and to know and trust their inner power.

when i felt and saw the sadness i could feel and see how deeply these angelic beings love us, i could feel their desire for humanity to stop punishing themselves and i could feel their understanding and acceptance of each persons choices to learn and grow within their own experience without judgement, they love us unconditionally. â¤  message from the angels.

children, we are all gods children and we are loved deeply. we suffer within your suffering and we do this to ease your individual burdens as you live your lives and express yourselves. each of you are a very special gift and you come from and will all return to your light. suffer not with that which was and is created by the flesh and know peace will follow.

our bodies are capable of building a whole human being cell by cell. we can give a baby all the nutrients they need for 9months without them consuming a drop of water or eating a mouthful of food themselves.

so for every person who frowns upon a woman breast feeding in public, i think you need to check on your opinions and why they are there. thereâ€™s little i could say is a more natural process in our world now.

i came to gems four years ago. at 20, i was a young mother and wanted to do the best by my son. however, i found myself with very few choices and close to no support. i fell into â€œthe lifeâ€ as a way to make ends meet for myself and my son. it wasnâ€™t the quick solution that i thought it might be, and there were times that i was even homeless. eventually, i received help and learned about the work that gems does. iâ€™ll always remember my first day at the center. i was scared and nervous, but the staff was very welcoming â€“ and i felt like going there was a good decision. within time, it felt like home. i received consistent case management at gems and regularly attended groups, which was one of the first steps to obtaining my financial independence. gems helped me strengthen my leadership skills as i became a mentor for the sista mentoring project and a participant in ei. within one year, i successfully completed my hha certification. since then, i have moved out of new york with my son, am working full-time as an hha and am looking forward to enrolling in college. #gemsgirls .

text:
sending love to black women and people w/ mental illness, w/ disabilities who live through hell most people won't, but whose experiences are invalidated, who are expected to be superhuman but your needs are unseen, and labeled defective when you need a break.

i know. i know that racism makes sexism look like love. mental health and disability discrimination makes racism look like respect. that rape makes the rest doable. 
i was sexually assaulted for over a decade as a child. my siblings, my friends were not. growing up i slept w/ a dresser barricading my door or stayed awake all night. i still have ptsd and night terrors. my siblings, my friends do not. 
but to hear them, they had harder lives.
my brothers claim more disadvantage because i was young when we left chicago. but every year growing up i went back, alone, for months to my unsafe chicago neighborhood because it was safer for me than wny. people can be animals whoâ€™ll try to use & abuse people like me for our looks, title, position, etc. my siblings don't need to worry about that. 
but they and white friends (in the white racist community i was raised in) claim less privilege because i was scouted to play college ball, i got into the best colleges. i had to fight more unfair systems & prejudices than the ones they claim handicapped them.
and when i couldn't get a good job in an insular, parochial and racist upstate ny legal community i opened my own law firm. by the time i closed it i was winning legal awards & being asking to run for judge.
i navigated, alone, through 80 hour weeks & the hyper stress of work where one mistake has dire consequences because when i became a lawyer i became the first professional in my orbit. but karen didn't change the office toner so their lives are harder. colleagues who can't have my resume, & who benefit from disability & mental health discrimination i'm harmed by, call me a flame out when i need a break. it's sad that my story is typical of black woman & people with disabilities. sharing it so anyone who thinks they're going it alone knows that they aren't. 
#love #blackqueen #blackwomenmatter #ptsd #ptsdawareness #disability #metoo

text:
<<< #menâ€™swork >>> over the past couple years-especially since the #metoo #movement began to prevail- there has been a massive uprising in #women standing in their #power. recently, i have noticed a great deal of men stepping up to â€œdo the workâ€ of personal and collective healing, #transformation and activation of the masculine. 
when we first decided to host the elemental retreat - i was apprehensive. mostly because i didnâ€™t think i was â€œman enoughâ€. my entire life- my relationship with men went something like - sexual abuse from a coach, followed by a lack of emotional support from all men, and a sad excuse for positive male role models in my particular chosen friend groups.. thank god for my mom to bake some common sense and value into me.. but when we decided to hit â€œgoâ€ on the #elemental evolved masculine immersion #retreat- it was a massive initiation for me. i really had to step up into my power as a man. organize. #empower. and actually believe it it! a few of the profound shift that happened along the way:

1. learned not to give a #fuck about what people think about me. i am a man. i have #emotions, #desires, needs, strengths, weaknesses, and they are all perfect. so often - as a man - i have found myself feeling as if i need to be strong all the time- but now i see so much beauty, even in the pain, #trauma, and #triumph of my brothers.

2. i gained an entirely new perception on the importance of values like honor (sacred union of the masculine and feminine), integrity (to myself and the other), kindness, and service (how are you showing up for your brothers)? these all deepened in my heart and mind this week as i began to revise my core values, as a man.

3. radical transparency- showing up to every situation with child- like curiosity, yet boldly speaking truth- even if it has the potential to scare someone away... essentially- in regards to the feminine- i aim to be able to speak my truth in order to no the #righteously aligned tribe will survive. 
4. #sacredsexuality- overall, a theme i see in my own life and through this retreat is the divine reunion of the sacred #masculine and #feminine. more on this soon.. my mind and heart are wide open

text:
according to the united nations office on drugs and crimeâ€™s global report on trafficking in persons, human trafficking has â€œhit a 13-year record high..â€ in 2016, there were over 25,000 cases of human trafficking reported, a 5,000 increase from 2003. although cases are being reported more consistently, with over 65 countries implementing different institutions to assist in collecting information, trafficking remains a crucial issue. there is no reason for a person to have a price tag on them. while progress has been made, we must continue to advocate for an end to this horrific occurrence happening across the globe. text:
babylon tings

the man wants to control how we talk about white supremacy. how we even express frustration with hate crimes. we are required to use a language of inclusion, love, solidarity, and take some of the responsibility ourselves as people of color and difference who have been eating shit since day one. 
i refuse!

i have a modest proposal for white people. the next time there are hateful acts from your community, stand up, take responsibility, and examine how you have been complicit. how has your mind state, consumption, voting patterns, or even just apathy enabled and perpetuated white supremacy. do you complain about a â€œwelfare stateâ€? do you complain about mexicans taking your jobs?  did you support single payer? have you ever talked about genetics and extra ligaments when watching ussain bolt run? look back perhaps on how youve responded when the #metoo movement started. rewind the tape on your feelings during the kavanaugh hearings? where were you at the bar, at work, or in class when people were screaming to invade iraq in the early-aughts? do you speak about the â€œinherent violenceâ€ in the quran? do you ever consider how the imf and world bank is bleeding the carribean to death? where were u for puerto rico during the hurricanes? 
if you arent consistently with us shooting in the gym on all fronts, you are complicit. you dont get to wake up when you want and post a victim of a hate crime like â€œyo this is so fucked up we all human why is it this way? i love my black friends. go patriots tho!â€ the next time a lil chinaman tells you to clean your shit up, maybe donâ€™t make it about you and your proximity to white supremacy. i dont care about your personal history or proximity to white supremacy. i just want it to end. that should be the focus. dont make it about you, make it about ending white supremacy because that is what still underlies every thing in this country. please and thank you.

.

i spoke at the opening event for a womenâ€™s conference last april in #sanfrancisco . i got to meet the lovely @ashley_judd. i am in awe of ashley and all the amazing women like her who speak up for #women and #womenempowerment. #pbwc. i meet women in every capacity of life, business and society who look out for one another and are working to make the world better. we can each make a difference and i speak up on issues that matter. your voice matters. this womenâ€™s event had me energized and inspired. â€¢
sometimes speaking up feels scary and isolating. even if no one stands up with you, it does not change your truth or the fact that others have their stories. and sometimes all it takes is a few brave people to stand up and inspire other people to stand up as they find their voice. never underestimate yourself and the power of speaking up. â€¢
such sisterhood. when we rise together, we make change. speak up, rise up. #womenliftingwomen #thursdaymotivation #tbt #sanfrancisco #laugh #love #picoftheday #business #conferencespeaker #metoo #timesup #womenbosses #riseuptogether

text:
#whatiwaswearing
.
this is what i was wearing on â€œthe nightâ€. the night that changed life forever.
.
i was wearing my ironman tank top. my dad bought me this tank top after cheering me on in the cold, wet rain for 14 hours and 11 minutes at ironman arizona in 2015. we bought it together in ironman village as my mom was chasing around my little boys only 6 and 4 at the time. ironman arizona was one of the proudest moments of my life. completing 140.6 miles on the coldest day arizona had all year, surrounded by my family and best friends. it was a dream. â¤ï¸
.
and then just a few years later, i was wearing this tank top. the one that represented pure joy, grit and made me smile each time i wore it ... and every ounce of joy was stripped from my terrified body when my worst nightmare came true.
this tank top.
ironman.
triathlon.
it all made me cringe remembering the aftermath of trauma. 6...7...8...months later trying to pick up the pieces of my life and sobbing alone in the darkness. .
i did complete another ironman. untrained. to prove i was â€œokâ€. to myself and everyone. but deep down my joy had been stripped from me and i was numb. and i started dropping races. oceanside 70.3, holidayman olympic and something i havenâ€™t talked about yet ... ironman louisville. i had to drop out and was fully refunded. i was supposed to toe the line of ironman 3 in 2018 in louisville. but now iâ€™m thankful i didnâ€™t.
.
my joy for my sport was stolen. i was numb for soooooo long. i hurt and cried and have been through the worst personal hell imaginable. and every time i flashback i see this tank top. that is why i didnâ€™t compete last year. that is why i probably blew it with two incredible companies i wanted to work with that took a chance on me....but for nothing i did wrong except the inability to deliver even one race...will likely back out for 2019. i couldnâ€™t face triathlon....
.
until now.
.
and now itâ€™s personal. after 10 months (and still ongoing) of intense therapy and my retreat in september... my mindset has shifted. i am here. i am fucking here. i am ready to take back what was stolen from me.
continued in commentsğŸ‘‡ğŸ½

female fiddler crabs and hens prefer males with extravagantly large claws and tails respectively. ewes (female rams) will mate with the ram that wins the brutal intrasexual head-butting contest. they reward targeted aggression by granting sexual access. needless to say, there are innumerable other examples of sexual selection that i might describe, but i suspect that you get the general gist. are rams exhibiting toxic masculinity? are female fiddler crabs succumbing to antiquated notions of masculinity as promulgated by the crab patriarchy?
.

text:
damp suns in disturbed skies
20â€ x 16â€. oil on linen. 2018 (title references baudelaire, a favorite poet of joâ€™s)
â€˜pink houses, charlestonâ€™ watercolor by jo nivison hopper. courtesy of the arthayer r. sanborn hopper collection trust. 
in 1924, the year of her marriage to edward hopper, jo nivison hopper was a well received artist in the new york art world - often shown in exhibitions alongside the likes of stuart davis and man ray. 
as an accomplished artist who eagerly embraced the most current modernist styles of the day, much more so than her husband did, jo captured in her vibrant and lyrical watercolors favored objects and sunny views of the scenic locales that she and edward often painted side by side.
this small building facing the cobblestones of chalmers street in historic charleston is commonly referred to as the pink house. built around 1712, it is believed to be the oldest remaining structure in the city. though called a house, the building originally served as a tavern and is rumored to have housed a brothel on the top floor.

text:

"teachers hit me - asking why i didn't return to korea with my father. my entire life, i have been made to feel as though i should not be there." to hear more stories, and for more information on the work we do, head to our website - link in bio!

text: a year ago today on january 30, 2018, something happened to me that kind of changed my life. this something had traumatized me. not only did i change as a person, but my mental illnesses got worse. since then, ive grown and became stronger, i made a best friend, and i've learned a lot about myself. im still finding ways to deal with my trauma, but i will never give up. i will continue to grow, even when i have a flashback or anxiety attack. my best friend helped me throughout all this, as we helped each other. all of my friends have helped me in some way, so has my best friend's family. thank you all for helping me for the past year, even when it seemed impossible. i love you all, i can't wait for the future and to get this traumatic event passed me, i can do it. my trauma doesnt define me or the person who was involved. i love my best friend and i wouldn't change what happened. im finally ready for the next chapter of my life. #metoo

text:
oftentimes, our struggle around safe sexual experiences is rooted in a secret developmental history of emotional neglect. yep â€” the early childhood experiences we had of either receiving the interpersonal nourishment we needed, or not, wires us into embodied expectations around whatâ€™s normal... .
_
for example, when our caretakers denied, downplayed, diminished or ignored our physical or emotional needs, we mightâ€™ve learned through osmosis to either deny them ourselves, embrace them with deviance or be hyper self-reliant around getting them met... .
_
having a regulated relationship to knowing, expressing and receiving our needs can be incredibly hard â€” foreign feeling, even. which is why itâ€™s so common for many of us to instead end up in sexual experiences that mirror our developmental experience of our feelings and needs not mattering.
_
as adults wanting healthy, nourishing and fulfilling sex lives, beginning to identify our needs and leaning into the vulnerability of voicing them... is central.
_
do you know what physical safety feels like for you in a relationship? how about in bed? do you know what emotional safety feels like for you â€” in a relationship and in bed? 
_
identifying what you need in order to feel safe is the first step to truly fulfilling sex. voicing your needs is the second. and then, of course, mmmm... receiving. â¤ï¸ .
_
some things that make meeee feel safe in bed: easy communication before, during & after, body praise & worship, mutual emotional admiration and respect, sharing std statuses, trusting i feel comfortable enough to pause if needed, trusting theyâ€™ll honor my pause, feeling free to be wild or tender or sad or soft or totally rolling in ecstasy.
_
what about you??
_
check my stories for the next 24 hrs for more on the link between developmental neglect & sexual exploitation. xo
_
sending you so much trust and care wherever you are on the journey!

text_retweet:
#repost @womensmarchjkt (@get_repost)
ãƒ»ãƒ»ãƒ»
update, 18.30 wib, 31 jan: kuota sudah penuh.  terima kasih atas ketertarikannya. nanti akan ada facebook live juga.

setelah kasus kekerasan seksual yang dialami seorang mahasiswi bernama agni di ugm diekspos oleh pers mahasiswa setempat, balairung press, ada peledakan pembahasan tentang kekerasan seksual di kampus universitas di seluruh indonesia.

tetapi kasus agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir. sayang sekali, banyak korban belum pernah mendapatkan keadilan dan malah diremehkan, dirundung, diintimidasi, dan dikeluarkan universitas.

mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

jakarta feminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan.

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (reporter, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

sekalian ada ada penyerahan oktovianus pogau award kepada citra dan thovan dari balairung press @bppmbalairung yogyakarta untuk keberanian dalam jurnalisme. selengkapnya ada di http://pantau.or.id/?/=d/789 
registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

http://bit.ly/metookampuswmj2019

text:
today she came through, 
through, with a scar on her hand,
with a bruise under the heart,
with a feel inside the chest,
cherishing a dwindling mess.
today she came with blood spilled all over,
tear-stained wound rolling,
marks unread, feelings unsaid,
words kept short and sentences incomplete,
yet, yet her punctuations were made very clear.
defined were the stops, they were fuller,
un-done, un-shed, unread,
her wounds increased,
they were more in halves, yet, deeper.
red turned blue, blue turned black,
white was unseen, yet peace more prominent,
she now wore more smiles than skirts,
more sleeves than leaves, more vain than pain.
her eyes spoke a thousand words,
her pupils dilated into nothingness, 
her lips chapped and her knuckles cracked,
her waist now, half the length. 
distances had reduced, but a bit too much,
peace or harmony, nothing as such,
blood dripped more but realisation struck less,
as sulking low had made her a big bad mess.
she was stuck yet resistant,
bold yet quiet,
known yet misunderstood,
she was like her dripping blood;
there, but unaware.
ages later, there were marks still,
scratches more, clots more, feels, less.
she gave in, gave in to the life and monotony,
that barely there symphony,
but she radiated unsaid energy,
she was powerful. she was made from the scars.
yet, her eyes numb, now spoke a thousand words,
her daughter came in the other day,
deep wounds, and blood dripping.
deep wounds. and,
blood dripping. -neeti

text:
my podcast @derekmansplains  is on hiatus currently but we will be dropping new episodes starting february 11th! in the meantime, here is a little #tbt to some episodes that i think are worth your time if you haven't listened yet! please subscribe, rate, review on @itunes @spotify and @stitcher give feedback at dmiapod@gmail.com! and check these eps to hold you over until 2/11!
-
-
ep. 3: "harv as a rock"w/anne victoria clark: my friend, comedian and tour mate anne clark talks with me about the #metoo movement, my bike getting stolen and being a viral sensation via dwayne "the rock" johnson's quoting of her work! anne has a new podcast called "the anne clark show" available on @itunes and stitcher. follow her on twitter: @annevclark
-
-
ep. 29: "chick-fil-gay" w/wanjiko eke: comedian wanjiko eke sits down to discuss her life as a gay black comic, my rose colored nostalgia and fake liberals! wanjiko has a new show in brooklyn called "rif comed: resistance is fertile" at pete's candy store. follow her on twitter: @wanjikoiam
-
-
ep. 33: "the lost science of science" w/dr. raj sivaraman: are white people at the top of the cultural food chain? is climate change real? dr. sivaraman is a comic, microbiologist and runner up on jeopardy. raj hosts a comedy show in new york called "monotony" where comedians and storytellers dive deep into the history of the most mundane things they are obsessed with. follow raj on twitter at: @rajsivaraman
-
-
ep. 40: "exploring whiteness" w/bryan yang. comic and writer bryan yang talk about his georgia roots, the hmong people and the man himself; ric flair! brian can be seen opening for the daily shows ronny chieng and you can follow him on twitter at: @bryanyang
-
-
ep. 43: "guys named brett" w/alison leiby. my wife joins alison and i to discuss the day-of appointment of supreme court justice brett kavanaugh and how they feel it affects the perception of women and their value as people. alison is a very funny comic who's written for "the opposition with jordan klepper", "the president show" and is now working on season 3 of the emmy and golden globe winning show "the marvelous mrs. maisel." follow alison on twitter at: @alisonlieby

text:
my podcast @derekmansplains  is on hiatus currently but we will be dropping new episodes starting february 11th! in the meantime, here is a little #tbt to some episodes that i think are worth your time if you haven't listened yet! please subscribe, rate, review on @itunes @spotify and @stitcher give feedback at dmiapod@gmail.com! and check these eps to hold you over until 2/11!
-
-
ep. 3: "harv as a rock"w/anne victoria clark: my friend, comedian and tour mate anne clark talks with me about the #metoo movement, my bike getting stolen and being a viral sensation via dwayne "the rock" johnson's quoting of her work! anne has a new podcast called "the anne clark show" available on @itunes and stitcher. follow her on twitter: @annevclark
-
-
ep. 29: "chick-fil-gay" w/wanjiko eke: comedian wanjiko eke sits down to discuss her life as a gay black comic, my rose colored nostalgia and fake liberals! wanjiko has a new show in brooklyn called "rif comed: resistance is fertile" at pete's candy store. follow her on twitter: @wanjikoiam
-
-
ep. 33: "the lost science of science" w/dr. raj sivaraman: are white people at the top of the cultural food chain? is climate change real? dr. sivaraman is a comic, microbiologist and runner up on jeopardy. raj hosts a comedy show in new york called "monotony" where comedians and storytellers dive deep into the history of the most mundane things they are obsessed with. follow raj on twitter at: @rajsivaraman
-
-
ep. 40: "exploring whiteness" w/bryan yang. comic and writer bryan yang talk about his georgia roots, the hmong people and the man himself; ric flair! brian can be seen opening for the daily shows ronny chieng and you can follow him on twitter at: @bryanyang
-
-
ep. 43: "guys named brett" w/alison leiby. my wife joins alison and i to discuss the day-of appointment of supreme court justice brett kavanaugh and how they feel it affects the perception of women and their value as people. alison is a very funny comic who's written for "the opposition with jordan klepper", "the president show" and is now working on season 3 of the emmy and golden globe winning show "the marvelous mrs. maisel." follow alison on twitter at: @alisonlieby
-
-

text:
dpr ri dukung ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual

wakil ketua komisi viii dewan perwakilan rakyat (dpr) ace hasan syadzily membantah rancangan undang-undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) diarahkan untuk mendukung pro-zina dan lesbian, gay, biseks, dan transgender (lgbt) "jadi tidak benar jika ada pandangan yang berkembang selama ini bahwa ruu pks akan diarahkan pada upaya memperbolehkan hubungan seksual suka sama suka [free sex] dan memperbolehkan hubungan seks sesama jenis," ujar ace, kamis (31/1/2019). terkait dengan ruu pks, ace menjelaskan sampai saat ini dpr komisi viii masih melakukan pembahasan di tingkat panitia kerja (panja). kata ace, dpr telah sepakat dengan panja pemerintah untuk membahas daftar inventaris masalah (dim). "kami akan menyandingkan antara dim yang kami miliki dengan dim yang dimiliki pemerintah," ucap ace.

https://tirto.id/wakil-ketua-komisi-viii-dpr-bantah-ruu-pks-disebut-pro-zina-amp-lgbt-dftb

text:
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar adaÂ umbrella actÂ lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakanÂ #metooÂ yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™Â beijing platform for actionÂ (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagiÂ qawwamÂ (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepadaÂ mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
â€”â€”

text:
i have the honor tonight of designing a tablescape for hear our stories by @upsetting_rape at @motorhousebaltimore. this edition of hear our stories is about celebrating black victim-survivors. this table was a special one to design. i will be honoring my mother, my sister, ancestors, friends, strangers, and myself through a light meal dedicated to active healing in 2019. as with all of my tablescapes there will be symbolism to each element. 
there will be cacao butter chia cornbread made with @eatsoular cacao butter (symbolizing wealth as nourishing and healthy relationships with our bodies and ourselves) and a remix of the classic rice and black-eyed peas dish hoppinâ€™ john (with the black eyed peas symbolizing the exploration of restorative justice in domestic violence, brown rice to symbolize prosperity in the path of healing, and adobo chiles to represent the concept of thriving versus surviving on the very linear path of healing). for even lighter nourishment i will also have my smoke on the water broth for sipping. it is a vegan broth i make with applewood smoked sun tea and garlic i ferment for 15 days. all foods served are vegan. please join us for this very special night of fellowship and reflection. #â¤ï¸#notalone #metoo #comestibledesign #fooddesign #tablescape #blackhealing #healingfoods

text:
i put my daughter on the bus minutes ago, and the chill wonâ€™t leave my bones. but you know what else leaves me stone cold? learning that former new york attorney general #ericschneiderman spent nearly $340,000 in campaign donations on lawyers. and specifically, on the lawyers representing him in investigations into his criminal sexual abuse of @mmanningbarish and others. theirs were the horrific stories, as retold by @newyorkermag, that led to his swift resignation last may.
....
campaign donations are supposed to help candidates amplify their message and publicize their accomplishments, not save them from felony charges. instead, new yorkers who gave schneiderman money when he was a national hero in the making unwittingly and unwillingly became his legal defense fund. this is sick, sad, and worst of all, legal in new york.
....
but #ericschneiderman did not just spent $340k of his votersâ€™ trust on criminal defense lawyers. he is still sitting on another $6.5 million in his campaign war chest, built in part on his reputation as a vigorous voice for womenâ€™s equality. his reps now say he will distribute the money to â€œworthy and appropriateâ€ causes. his victims are convinced he will give the money to yoga and meditation centers that will give him refuge in exchange for big bucks. there is only one â€œworthy and appropriateâ€ cause here: womenâ€™s fight to be free from gender-based violence. many of us applauded eric schneiderman when he was a voice for choice. in my own life as an activist, i posed for pictures with him at fundraisers; gave him standing ovations at rallies. survivors and allies: #ericschneiderman may be gone from public view, but his actions still undermine our movement and threaten our bodies. letâ€™s demand he give his money instead to orgs like @sffny @safehorizon and @timesup. #trustwomen #standwithsurvivors #michellemanningbarish #metoo

text:
letâ€™s try something out shall we?
.
if i ask â€œhow are you?â€ you respond how...iâ€™m good, fine, okay usually right?

see, technically those arenâ€™t feelings they are just safe, surface level fillers we all (hi #metoo ) use because itâ€™s easy and we are programmed to automatically respond in social interactions.

okay, now letâ€™s try this: howâ€™s your heart?

see what i did there? i didnâ€™t ask how are you so you could just skip the saga and fill it with a good fine whatever. i asked how your heart is. which sure, you could say fine but my bet is youâ€™re going to respond with the truth. youâ€™re going to give me more depth.

we can embrace our humanness, be more real and redefine how we connect by first simply shifting our language and how we talk to one another.

iâ€™ve been deliberately asking this to everyone i come in contact with over the last year and let me tell ya, itâ€™s amazing what happens when you give someone some breathing room to be real.

try it out. ask your bff, your coworker, your mom, the barista. report back. letâ€™s #relcaimwhatsreal by connecting heart to heart

text:
where will #metoo take its survivors? 
itâ€™s a question that we, at the polis project, tried to deal with in our conversations last year even as women survivors were coming out with devastating, chilling testimonies, one after another. 
considering the history of silence, it isnâ€™t a surprise that most conversations in the media remained confined to survivor testimonies per se. in an effort to add to the larger conversation, we began with an obvious question: what was â€œnextâ€ for the survivors, those who remained anonymous and those who came out to identify their perpetrators? how do we understand the culture of fear and silence that remains? what did #metoo mean in hard, legal terms for the victims, and the perpetrators? or, what kind of legal challenges did survivor testimonies raise, and for whom? how could the survivors possibly face these challenges, particularly considering their vulnerability on one hand and, often, the power and influence of the men they accused? what paths lead to justice? is there anything that can vastly minimize sexual violence? 
the work thatâ€™s emerged thereafter couldnâ€™t be confined to these questionsâ€”there can be no clarity towards the future without constantly delving in the past, and the present. this small body of work seeks to do that without taking its eyes off the question: what comes â€œafterâ€ #metoo? 
beginning tomorrow, the polis project will publish work featuring apoorva karagappa, jhuma sen, kruthika ns, nayema nasir, raya sarkar, rollie mukherjee, suchitra vijayan, and vasundhara sirnate. 
do read, and share! 
write to us at feedback@thepolisproject.com.

text:
warning: sexual assault/harassment/rape

i was 15, he was 16. he was my first boyfriend. we did (unfortunately still do) karate together. we had been dating for 2 months and he started pushing the idea of sex. i told him no every time. on february 4th of this year, we were alone in his basement in his bedroom and he threw me down on his bed and started aggressively making out with me. i couldn't get away. i tried turning my head and kicking my legs and and yelling for him to stop. but it was useless, he had me pinned down and my arms above my head, his tongue down my throat and if i yelled anymore i might puke. it seemed like an eternity. he put his hands up my shirt and groped my butt and my boobs and when i moved his hand, he moved it back. i told him no, he said it's fine just kissing! it is not fine! it was not just kissing! this happened more than once during the six months we dated. i only consented to kissing him maybe twice. 
he is the reason i don't trust men, the reason i'm terrified to date. i can't even handle being in class with him at karate. i had a panic attack last week as soon as i walked off that floor because he was next to me the whole class grinning. i don't even know how i hold myself together. i see home every single day at school, he stares at me during lunch and across the hall from his classroom into mine. i wish he could feel the pain he put me through. 
i feel like that day is all i think about. the fact that i know i'm not the only one he assulted, and there is nothing that i can do to protect anyone from him because they won't believe he could do such a thing. he seems like a nice, innocent guy until you're alone with him. i reported it, but he is still walking, and taunting me every single day of my life. this "sweet innocent" guy hit me and hurt me in ways that will affect me and other girls for the rest of our lives. and the worst part is that so many others have gone through the same thing and these pigs feel no remorse. #metoo #metoomovement #nomore

i was 15, he was 16. he was my first boyfriend. we did (unfortunately still do) karate together. we had been dating for 2 months and he started pushing the idea of sex. i told him no every time. on february 4th of this year, we were alone in his basement in his bedroom and he threw me down on his bed and started aggressively making out with me. i couldn't get away. i tried turning my head and kicking my legs and and yelling for him to stop. but it was useless, he had me pinned down and my arms above my head, his tongue down my throat and if i yelled anymore i might puke. it seemed like an eternity. he put his hands up my shirt and groped my butt and my boobs and when i moved his hand, he moved it back. i told him no, he said it is fine just kissing! it is not fine! it was not just kissing! this happened more than once during the six months we dated. i only consented to kissing him maybe twice. 
he is the reason i do not trust men, the reason i am terrified to date. i can not even handle being in class with him at karate. i had a panic attack last week as soon as i walked off that floor because he was next to me the whole class grinning. i do not even know how i hold myself together. i see home every single day at school, he stares at me during lunch and across the hall from his classroom into mine. i wish he could feel the pain he put me through. 
i feel like that day is all i think about. the fact that i know i am not the only one he assulted, and there is nothing that i can do to protect anyone from him because they will not believe he could do such a thing. he seems like a nice, innocent guy until you are alone with him. i reported it, but he is still walking, and taunting me every single day of my life. this "sweet innocent" guy hit me and hurt me in ways that will affect me and other girls for the rest of our lives. and the worst part is that so many others have gone through the same thing and these pigs feel no remorse. #metoo #metoomovement #nomore

text_retweet:
reposted from @muslimahnewsid - / perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar adaÂ umbrella actÂ lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakanÂ #metooÂ yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™Â beijing platform for actionÂ (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagiÂ qawwamÂ (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepadaÂ mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
â€”â€”
follow @muslimahnewsid
.
#muslimahnews #muslimahnewsid 
#khilafahajaranislam 
#selamatkanperempuan
#tolakruupks 
#islamsolusinegeri - #regrann

text:
a bedazzling lady, so bold and beautiful,
seeks a companion who for her is suitable.
she dreams of a man with a heart of gold,
searching for the one who would fit in her fantasy's mould.
she looks for,
beauty and valour personified in his every aspect,
with charm and grace his soul bedecked.
his smile, calm like the subtle waves of the sea,
like the string of pearls sparkling with glee.
his eyes, brilliant like a diamond so pure,
the dauntless pride in them graciously allure.
his moustache with pride they curl,
so gallant, a head-turner for every girl.
his chest strong and broad with honor, 
his charisma so magnetic, many hearts he conquer.
his love, like the a vivid pallet of million colors beams through his heart,
the virility in his soul is what makes him different, from others he's worlds apart.
all she wants is a chivalrous, courageous, gentleman for sure,
her perfect soulmate who, like her, is angelic to the core.
. Â©shwetha @shwetha_rishi
________________________________
a woman needs and wants a man who is not afraid to show his sensitive side. who owns who he is with pride. who's not reluctant to show his love for her, who respects her and her family and her wishes. who works hard to make her dreams come true the same way he works for his. 
a woman seeks a gentleman who's the exact mirror image of her soul, the perfect soulmate.
#shespeaksforthechange #herstory #proudtobeawoman #girlpower #genderroles #genderequality #metoomovement #metooÂ  #she #her #sheisme #shespeaks #shewrites

text:
sheets of empty canvas
untouched sheets of clay
were laid spread out before me
as her body once did
all five horizons
revolved around her soul
as the earth to the sun
now the air i tasted and breathed
has taken a turn

oh and all i taught her was everything
oh i know she gave me all that she wore
and now my bitter hands
chafe beneath the clouds
of what was everything
oh the pictures have
all been washed in black
tattooed everything
i take a walk outside
i'm surrounded by
some kids at play
i can feel their laughter
so why do i sear
oh, and twisted thoughts that spin
round my head
i'm spinning
oh, i'm spinning
how quick the sun can, drop away

text:
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar adaÂ umbrella actÂ lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakanÂ #metooÂ yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™Â beijing platform for actionÂ (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagiÂ qawwamÂ (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepadaÂ mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
â€”â€”

.

text:
kasus #agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir

mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

@jakartafeminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (reporter, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

selain itu, ada penyerahan oktovianus pogau award kepada citra dan thovan dari balairung press @bppmbalairung yogyakarta untuk keberanian dalam jurnalisme. selengkapnya ada di http://pantau.or.id/?/=d/789 
registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

http://bit.ly/metookampuswmj2019

see ya there!

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
last night while i was going back home, two men followed me on their bike. they passed rude comments, and made offensive voices. 
i was paranoid! i was angry about the fact that even after all these campaigns, confessions, allegations and awareness, there are people who just donâ€™t stop! i questioned myself why are we doing all this, if it is not changing anything?
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
that is when i realised that when they were doing it all, i had the guts to take out my phone and make a video of their rude behaviour.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
that is when i realised that all these campaigns and struggles may not change others, but yes, they have a given me and many others the strength to fight and react to it. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
the truth is, yes, some people may never change and this may never stop. but better truth is, we wonâ€™t be oppressed by it now. we will act.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
till now we have been looking for heroes. but little did we know we are becoming one. â˜ºï¸

text: found this old junction box on a recent rewire. labelled "the g box" i had to have it for my vintage electrical collection. with old lead cables terminating within it, the little piece of history dates back to the 1940s. although this house was rewired in the 1970s i assume the electricians back then didn't care too much about removing the previous cables? with my rewire (2018) i removed all i could of the now rare materials.  #thegbox #old #oldhouse #vintage #rewire #9thedition #18thedition #leadcables #live #stuffifind #bs7671 #electriciansofinstagram #tools #photooftheday

text:
setelah kasus kekerasan seksual yang dialami seorang mahasiswi bernama agni di ugm diekspos oleh pers mahasiswa setempat, balairung press, ada peledakan pembahasan tentang kekerasan seksual di kampus universitas di seluruh indonesia. tetapi kasus agni bukan kasus kekerasan seksual pertama yang terjadi di kampus, dan tentu bukan kasus terakhir. sayang sekali, banyak korban belum pernah mendapatkan keadilan dan malah diremehkan, dirundung, diintimidasi, dan dikeluarkan universitas.
mengapa kekerasan seksual sering terjadi di kampus universitas, dan dilakukan baik mahasiswa maupun dosen? apakah gerakan #metoo yang sudah sangat mengubah perilaku dan cara berpikir di negara lain bisa berhasil di indonesia juga? dan bagaimana kita bisa membantu menghilangkan kekerasan seksual di kampus?

jakarta feminist discussion group (jfdg) dan yayasan pantau menyelenggarakan 'diskusi kekerasan seksual dan gerakan #metoo di kampus' sebagai bagian dari rangkaian pra-acara women's march jakarta pada sabtu, 9 februari 2019 pukul 9.30 s.d. 13.00 wib di ruang komunal (facebook), one pacific place, senayan.

dimoderatori febriana firdaus (wartawan, jakarta), diskusi ini dihadiri pembicara
1. citra maudy (editor, balairung press, universitas gadjah mada, yogyakarta)
2. evi mariani (editor, the jakarta post, jakarta)
3. saras dewi (dosen, universitas indonesia, depok)

registrasi bisa dilakukan di formulir berikut. tempat terbatas!

http://bit.ly/metookampuswmj2019

#bastraindo #womensmarchjkt #beranibersuara #metoo #hearmetoo #akujuga @dearcatcallers.id

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
but wylie wasnâ€™t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: â€œinformation operationsâ€, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us militaryâ€™s doctrine of the â€œfive-dimensional battle spaceâ€. his brief ranged across the scl group â€“ the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as â€œmi6 for hireâ€, and iâ€™d never quite understood it.
.
- itâ€™s like dirty mi6 because youâ€™re not constrained. thereâ€™s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. itâ€™s normal for a â€˜market research companyâ€™ to amass data on domestic populations. and if youâ€™re working in some country and thereâ€™s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well thatâ€™s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though itâ€™s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, â€˜oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.â€™
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer â€“ the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates â€“ and his daughter rebekah.

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
how common are false allegations of rape or sexual assault?

one commonly cited figure holds that 5 percent of rape allegations are found to be false, but that figure paints a very incomplete picture, says belknap. typically, this figure comes from studies done on college students, an estimated 95 percent of whom do not report their assaults to police. overall, an estimated 8 to 10 percent of women are thought to report their rapes to the police, which means that â€” at the very highest â€” we can infer that 90 percent of rapes go unreported, says belknap. obviously, only those rapes that are reported in the first place can be considered falsely reported, so that 5 percent figure only applies to 10 percent (at most) of rapes that occur. this puts the actual false allegation figure closer to 0.5 percent.

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaignâ€™s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleâ€™s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there â€œcould have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheatingâ€. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesdayâ€™s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian
